data:
Specifies power in milliwatts during static power calculation or piecewise linear ( -pwl ) current waveform, during dynamic power calculation for cell or instance. The command accepts a unit specification (e.g. 10w). 
 The format of the PWL waveform is: { time1 current1 time2 current2 ... time_n current_n } 
 Time is in ns and current in mA. 
 Example : 
 set_power -pwl -pg_net {} -cell BUFX2MTL {0 0 10 0 10.1 5 10.5 0} 
 Here, at 0ns its value is 0mA , at 10ns its value is 0mA , at 10.1ns its value is 5mA , and so on.

