data:
Specifies additional options that are to be used with the read_spef command run in the boundary model generation session. The options specified with the -spef_options parameter are appended to the read_spef command. 
 For example, if the boundary model is to be generated from a session that uses a view definition, the -spef_options parameter can be used to specify the rc_corner, as shown in the following command: create_cell_signal_em_model … -spef files -spef_options {-rc_corner corner1} 
 The -spef_options parameter must be specified with the -spef parameter.
